description: I am the original owner of the corvette. I bought it in 1979 before husband and kids (when I actually had play money). I taught second grade for 38 years so a little old schoolteacher actually owns this car. I was saving it for my son but he prefers trucks, go figure. We only drove it from May to September then put it up for the winter. My dad and brother were mechanics and kept it in great condition. I have all the original paperwork so I will list some of the things that it has as I am not mechanical.
5.7 liter (350 CID)' 4-BBL V8 engine RPO L48
Steel belted radial tires- 2 are new
T roof, C-4 9 electric rear window defogger,MX1 automatic transmissionN90 aluminum wheels, power antenna,  K30 speed control
Has an air conditioner but it uses freon which is no longer legal - I know some of my friends have converted their air conditioner but I never did, AM FM radio with cassette

For sale in our Louisville Showroom is a very desirable 1979 Chevrolet Corvette with some serious power. The Chevrolet Corvette is labeled Americas Sports Car ever since its arrival in 1953. The Chevrolet Corvette is known as the best bang-for-buck sports car on the market and has had a strong fan-base since the first Corvette rolled off the line. This specific Corvette sports the last body style for the Third Generation Corvette (C3). In 1980 the front fascia was revised on the Corvette and this style was carried on until the end of the third generation Corvettes making the 1979 body style the last of its breed. This specific Corvette is sporting a Porsche Red paint that does a great job at showing off this Vettes body lines. The lengthy curvy front end of this Vette is definitely one of the best attributes of the third generation Corvettes which give it the ultimate sports car stance. The interior is a very clean tan leather interior that just received a fresh detail. The Tan interior looks absolutely stunning with the sunshine beaming through the open T-Tops as youre cruising down your favorite winding road. New Tires Brake pads calipers and master cylinder were done in May of 2018. This Corvettes power-plant is a very capable 350 Ci V8 that puts out some serious power. The motor was replaced less than 1000 miles ago. This potent engine is paired to a smooth shifting TH350 3 Speed Automatic transmission making it very comfortable cruising. This super clean Corvette is an excellent example of a well kept C3. This Corvette has a ton of options including; AM/FM Cassette Leather interior Power Steering Power Brakes Power Windows power locks seat belts Cruise Control Tilt Wheel and Air Conditioning. This Vette rests on its original wheels wrapped in Radial tires. This Corvette is a true driver that is ready to be your weekend warrior.
